<subSubSection id="C3146527FFF1E502531A818160AAF8F5" pageId="48" pageNumber="165" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFF1E502531A818160AAF8F5" blockId="48.[831,1437,1673,1857]" pageId="48" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF1E502531A818160A5F915" bold="true" box="[831,942,1673,1697]" pageId="48" pageNumber="165">Comment</emphasis>
: This probably undescribed species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFF1E50253A381A260EBF975" baseAuthorityName="KRAATZ" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[902,992,1705,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFF1E50253A381A260EBF975" box="[902,992,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="165">Z. hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and is characterized by dense and rather coarse punctation of the forebody and by darkbrown antennae with the apical three antennomeres pale-yellowish (body length: 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFF1E5025452800167C0F895" box="[1143,1227,1801,1825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="48" pageNumber="165" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFF1E502531A8021609EF8F5" box="[831,917,1833,1857]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="48" pageNumber="165" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
